 Media Spokesperson of Transport and Cummunity Safety Liaison, Mr Moeti Mmusi confirmed that commuters of a midibus were killed and injured when a truck rear-ended the midibus and went on to collide with another truck. 18 passengers had to be transported to the Middelburg Provincial Hospital and two were killed in the collision. Police are busy with an investigation, to conclude what caused the accident.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za